---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="The thesis behind Verified Software Bases — and why this exists even as AI makes software cheap."
>
  <section class="container-page pt-14 pb-10 md:pt-20">
    <p class="kicker">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-fg sm:text-5xl text-balance">
      A bet on judgment, not tokens.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-8 max-w-3xl">
    <div class="space-y-6 text-[16px] text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      <p>
        AI will make software generation cheap, fast, and abundant. That doesn't
        eliminate value — it moves value away from raw code generation and toward
        things that don't get cheaper:
      </p>
      <ul class="grid gap-2.5 border-l border-line pl-5">
        <li>— creator judgment</li>
        <li>— verified outcomes</li>
        <li>— trusted packaging</li>
        <li>— live previews</li>
        <li>— source ownership</li>
        <li>— remixability</li>
        <li>— launch support</li>
        <li>— honest curation</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Verified Software Bases doesn't sell "AI-generated code." That's becoming
        a commodity, fast. It sells <span class="text-fg">verified, scoped, ownable
        software outcomes</span> — each one previewed, reviewed, and packaged with
        a clear path from "looks interesting" to "deployed and earning".
      </p>

      <div class="panel-2 p-6 not-prose">
        <p class="kicker">Customer-facing thesis</p>
        <blockquote class="mt-2 text-xl font-medium text-fg text-balance">
          Skip the blank prompt. Start from verified software.
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <p>
        You can probably ask AI to build something similar. This exists for when
        you want the working version, the source code, the tradeoffs, and a path
        to launch — without managing the messy first pass yourself.
      </p>

      <p class="text-fg">
        Built, not curated. Verified, not promised. Ownable, not rented.
      </p>
      <p class="pt-4 border-t border-line">
        Today every Base on this site is mine. If that changes — if someone sends in
        work I'd be proud to list alongside my own — I'll open submissions formally.
        For now: <a class="link text-accent" href="/collab">/collab</a> is the door.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-12 pb-24">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/bases" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Bases →</a>
      <a href="/collab" class="btn btn-ghost">Collab</a>
      <a href="/trust" class="btn btn-naked text-sm">How I verify →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
